# DESCRIPTION
# Use the inclusion/exclusion principle to determine
# the number of elements in a set
# WeBWorK problem written by Michael E. O'Sullivan
# and Thomas Schmidt
# ENDDESCRIPTION

## DBsubject('Discrete Mathematics')
## DBchapter('Set Theory')
## DBsection('The Inclusion Exclusion Principle')
## KEYWORDS('')
## TitleText1('')
## EditionText1('')
## AuthorText1('')
## Section1('')
## Problem1('')
## Author('Thomas Schmidt','Michael E. O'Sullivan')
## Institution('SDSU')


############################
# Initialization

DOCUMENT();

loadMacros(
"PGstandard.pl",
"MathObjects.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());

############################
# Setup

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 0;

$nA = 100;
$nB = 200;
$nC = 300;
$nAintB = 10;
$nAintC = 15;
$nBintC = 20;
$nAintBintC = 5;

$answer = Compute($nA + $nB + $nC - $nAintB - $nAintC - $nBintC + $nAintBintC);

############################
# Main Text

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT
$BR
For help with these problems, please see
\{ htmlLink( "http://www-rohan.sdsu.edu/~mosulliv/Courses/discrete12f/sets.pdf", "this page" ) \}. $PAR
Suppose \(N(A) = $nA\), \(N(B) = $nB\), \(N(C) = $nC\) $BR
\(N(A\cap B) = $nAintB\), \(N(A\cap C) = $nAintC\), \(N(B\cap C) = $nBintC\) $BR
\(N(A\cap B\cap C) = $nAintBintC\) $BR
\(N(A\cup B\cup C) =\) \{ans_rule(5)\}
$BR
$BR
END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

############################
# Answer Evaluation

ANS($answer->cmp());

############################
# Solution

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR Solution: $PAR
The general formula for the inclusion/exclusion principle is $BR
\(N(A\cup B\cup C) = N(A) + N(B) + N(C) - N(A\cap B) - N(A\cap C) - N(B\cap C) + N(A\cap B\cap C)\) $PAR
Since we have $PAR 
\(N(A) = $nA,\) $BR
\(N(B) = $nB,\) $BR
\(N(C) = $nC,\) $BR
\(N(A\cap B) = $nAintB,\) $BR
\(N(A\cap C) = $nAintC,\) $BR
\(N(B\cap C) = $nBintC,\) $BR
\(N(A\cap B\cap C) = $nAintBintC\), $PAR
then the answer is $PAR
\($nA + $nB + $nC - $nAintB - $nAintC - $nBintC + $nAintBintC = $answer\) $BR
END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;

ENDDOCUMENT();
